---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AntColonySimulator from '../components/solid/AntColonySimulator';
---

<Layout title="Ant Colony Simulation">
	<main class="container mx-auto p-4">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Ant Colony Simulation</h1>
		
		<div class="flex justify-center mb-8">
			<AntColonySimulator client:load />
		</div>

		<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">How it Works</h2>
			<p class="mb-4">
				This simulation models a colony of ants foraging for food. Here's a breakdown of the components and rules:
			</p>
			<ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
				<li><span class="font-semibold">Blue Circle:</span> The nest, where the ants start and return to with food.</li>
				<li><span class="font-semibold">Green Circle:</span> The food source.</li>
				<li><span class="font-semibold">White Dots:</span> The ants.</li>
				<li><span class="font-semibold text-green-400">Green Pheromone Trail:</span> When an ant finds food and returns to the nest, it leaves a green pheromone trail that other ants can follow to the food source.</li>
			</ul>
			<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Ant Behavior</h3>
			<ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
				<li>Ants start at the nest and explore randomly, searching for food.</li>
				<li>If an ant finds a green pheromone trail, it has a high probability of following it.</li>
				<li>When an ant reaches the food source, it picks up food and starts returning to the nest.</li>
				<li>On its way back to the nest, the ant leaves a green pheromone trail.</li>
				<li>Once the ant reaches the nest, it drops off the food and goes back to foraging.</li>
                                <li>After 10 ants have returned to the nest with food, the food source will move to a new random location.</li>
			</ol>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
